'''[[aqua]] [[regia]]''' 

# An extremely powerful acid mixture composed of 3 parts concentrated [[hydrochloric acid]] to 1 part concentrated [[nitric acid]].  The name is Latin for ''royal water'' and is so named because it is one of the few [[solvent]]s capable of dissolving [[noble metals]] such as [[gold]] and [[platinum]].  (Extremely corrosive and dangerous.)

